<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-05T08:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-05T08:35:00-05:00" n="545" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d545">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/598: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-05T17:00:00+03:25">May 5,
                                    1943—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 8:19 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>466. Medjliss yesterday passed law granting Millspaugh powers
                            substantially as outlined in my 385, April 14. Full text being sent by
                            air mail.<note n="28" xml:id="d545fn28">Despatch No. 556, May 20, not
                                printed.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>